What Are Food Safety Audit and Certification Services?
Food Safety Audit and Certification Services are professional compliance assessment solutions provided by accredited third-party organizations to verify whether food manufacturers, processors, distributors, farms, retailers, and food service businesses comply with national regulations and internationally recognized food safety standards.
These services involve comprehensive inspections of production facilities, quality management systems, operational procedures, hygiene practices, traceability systems, and risk management protocols. Following successful evaluations, organizations receive certifications under globally accepted standards such as BRCGS, FSSC 22000, ISO 22000, GLOBALG.A.P., HACCP, and other Global Food Safety Initiative (GFSI)-recognized schemes, enabling them to strengthen consumer confidence, access international markets, and reduce operational risks.
As global food supply chains become increasingly interconnected, food safety certification has evolved from a regulatory requirement into a strategic business advantage that supports brand reputation, export opportunities, and long-term supply chain resilience.
